President Trump gave a speech at the United Nations on religious freedom. He expressed his pride in being the first U.S. President to host such a meeting and called for an end to religious persecution around the world. He highlighted the importance of protecting the rights of people of all faiths and announced a coalition of U.S. businesses for the protection of religious freedom. Trump also mentioned specific instances of religious attacks and violence, emphasizing the need for increased prosecution and punishment of such crimes. He concluded by urging all nations to join the U.S. in promoting religious liberty.